nodes.Description: Grants permission to describe requests and associated products in the Private Marketplace. This action can be performed by any account in an AWS Organization, provided the user has permissions to do so, and the Organization's Service Control Policies allow it
Grants permission to users to get a list of terms for an agreement
Grants permission to users to list their incoming subscription requests (for providers who provide products that require subscription verification)
Grants permission to users to list their subscription requests for products that require subscription verification
Grants permission to list existing change sets
Grants permission to list existing entities
Grants permission to users to list their private offers

Grants permission to get a queryable list for requests and associated products in the Private Marketplace. This action can be performed by any account in an AWS Organization, provided the user has permissions to do so, and the Organization's Service Control Policies allow it
Grants permission to list existing tasks
Grants permission to users to search their agreements
Grants permission to users to see their account's subscriptions
Grants permission to delete the resource policy of an existing entity
Grants permission to attach a resource policy to an existing entity
Grants permission to users to describe the metadata about the agreement
Describes Image Builds identified by a build Id
Grants permission to return the details of an existing change set
Grants permission to return the details of an existing entity

Grants permission to describe the Procurement System integration configuration (e.g. Coupa) for the individual account, or for the entire AWS Organization if one exists. This action can only be performed by the master account if using an AWS Organization
Grants permission to return the details of an existing task
Grants permission to users to view the details of their incoming subscription requests (for providers who provide products that require subscription verification)
Grants permission to users to view the details of their subscription requests for data products that require subscription verification
Retrieves entitlement values for a given product. The results can be filtered based on customer identifier or product dimensions
Grants permission to get the resource policy of an existing entity
Grants permission to view a seller dashboard
Lists Image Builds.
Grants permission to users to view details of the entitlements associated with an agreement. Note that this action is not applicable to Marketplace purchases
Grants permission to list tags on an existing entity or a change set
Grants permission to tag a deployment parameter resource
Grants permission to untag a deployment parameter resource
Grants permission to users to approve an incoming subscription request (for providers who provide products that require subscription verification)
Grants permission to users to accept their agreement requests. Note that this action is not applicable to Marketplace purchases

Grants permission to approve a request for a product to be associated with the Private Marketplace. This action can be performed by any account in an AWS Organization, provided the user has permissions to do so, and the Organization's Service Control Policies allow it
Grants permission to post metering records for a set of customers for SaaS applications
Grants permission to users to cancel their agreements. Note that this action is not applicable to Marketplace purchases
Grants permission to users to cancel pending subscription requests for products that require subscription verification
Grants permission to cancel a running change set
Grants permission to complete an existing task and submit the content to the associated change
Grants permission to users to create an agreement request. Note that this action is not applicable to Marketplace purchases

Grants permission to create a new request for a product or products to be associated with the Private Marketplace. This action can be performed by any account in an in an AWS Organization, provided the user has permissions to do so, and the Organization's Service Control Policies allow it

Grants permission to decline a request for a product to be associated with the Private Marketplace. This action can be performed by any account in an AWS Organization, provided the user has permissions to do so, and the Organization's Service Control Policies allow it
Grants permission to emit metering records
Grants permission to create or update a deployment parameter resource

Grants permission to create or update the Procurement System integration configuration (e.g. Coupa) for the individual account, or for the entire AWS Organization if one exists. This action can only be performed by the master account if using an AWS Organization

Grants permission to to verify that the customer running your paid software is subscribed to your product on AWS Marketplace, enabling you to guard against unauthorized use. Meters software use per ECS task, per hour, with usage prorated to the second
Grants permission to users to decline an incoming subscription requests (for providers who provide products that require subscription verification)
Grants permission to resolve a registration token to obtain a CustomerIdentifier and product code
Starts an Image Build

Grants permission to request a new change set (Note: resource-level permissions for this action and condition context keys for this action are only supported when used with Catalog API and are not supported when used with AWS Marketplace Management Portal)

Grants permission to users to subscribe to AWS Marketplace products. Includes the ability to send a subscription request for products that require subscription verification. Includes the ability to enable auto-renewal for an existing subscription
Grants permission to users to remove subscriptions to AWS Marketplace products. Includes the ability to disable auto-renewal for an existing subscription

Grants permission to users to make changes to an incoming subscription request, including the ability to delete the prospective subscriber's information (for providers who provide products that require subscription verification)
Grants permission to update the contents of an existing task

policy.Description: Provides the ability to review AWS Marketplace subscriptions
Provides the ability to subscribe and unsubscribe to AWS Marketplace software

Provides the ability to subscribe and unsubscribe to AWS Marketplace software, allows users to manage Marketplace software instances from the Marketplace 'Your Software' page, and provides administrative access to EC2.
Provides full access to AWS Marketplace Metering.
This policy grants permissions to view resources and basic metadata across all AWS services.
This policy grants permissions to troubleshoot and resolve issues in an AWS account. This policy also enables the user to contact AWS support to create and manage cases.
Provides read access to AWS Marketplace Entitlements
Provides read only access to Amazon SageMaker via the AWS Management Console and SDK.
Provides full access to Amazon SageMaker via the AWS Management Console and SDK. Also provides select access to related services (e.g., S3, ECR, CloudWatch Logs).
Provides full access to AWS Marketplace Private Image Build Feature. In addition to create private images, it also provides permissions to add tags to images, launch and terminate ec2 instances.
Provides full access to all administrative actions for an AWS Private Marketplace.
Provides full access to all administrative actions for an AWS Marketplace eProcurement integration.
Provides full access to all seller operations on the AWS Marketplace and other AWS services such as AMI management.
Provides sellers full access to AWS Marketplace Management Products page and other AWS services such as AMI management.
Provide sellers read-only access to AWS Marketplace Management Products page.
Used by AWS IQ to execute payment requests on behalf of a customer
Provides access to creating requests in an AWS Private Marketplace.
Grants read-only access to AWS Data Exchange and AWS Marketplace actions using the AWS Management Console and SDK.

Grants data subscriber access to AWS Data Exchange and AWS Marketplace actions using the AWS Management Console and SDK. It also provides select access to related services needed to take full advantage of AWS Data Exchange.

Grants data provider access to AWS Data Exchange and AWS Marketplace actions using the AWS Management Console and SDK. It also provides select access to related services needed to take full advantage of AWS Data Exchange.

Grants full access to AWS Data Exchange and AWS Marketplace actions using the AWS Management Console and SDK. It also provides select access to related services needed to take full advantage of AWS Data Exchange.
Provides permissions to register a resource and track usage through AWS Marketplace Metering Service.
This policy provides the permissions required to manage the Red Hat OpenShift Service on AWS (ROSA) subscription.
Provides full access for creating and managing the Vendor Insights resources
Provides read-only access for viewing the Vendor Insights resources
Provides full access for viewing entitled Vendor Insights resources and managing Vendor Insights subscriptions
Provides permissions to describe and update Private Marketplace resources and describe AWS Organizations
Enables access to AWS Services and Resources used or managed by AWS Marketplace for Resale Authorization.
